---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About - ADHD Treatment Directory India" activePage="about" description="About the ADHD Treatment Directory for India. Learn how verification works, how to contribute, and find crisis resources.">
  <section class="info-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About This Directory</h1>
      <p class="about-intro">
        People with ADHD in India — and their caregivers — often struggle to find psychiatrists or clinics that take ADHD seriously, offer proper assessments, and provide clear logistics. This directory exists to end the "call, get dismissed, try again" cycle.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section" style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>How Verification Works</h2>
      <div class="info-grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3><span class="badge badge-unverified">Unverified</span></h3>
          <p>Submitted but not yet reviewed by a maintainer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3><span class="badge badge-reviewed">Reviewed</span></h3>
          <p>Checked for completeness. Links and location validated by a maintainer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3><span class="badge badge-community-verified">Community Verified</span></h3>
          <p>Confirmed by 2+ independent sources or a recent patient report.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3><span class="badge badge-stale">Stale</span></h3>
          <p>Last verified over 12 months ago, or 2+ reports of being unreachable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section" style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How do I submit a listing?</h3>
          <p>Go to the <a href="/submit">Submit page</a>, fill in the structured form, and click submit. This generates a prefilled GitHub Issue. No account is needed beyond a free GitHub account.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How do I report incorrect or stale information?</h3>
          <p>Every listing has a "Report issue" button. Click it to open a prefilled GitHub Issue describing the problem. You can also file an issue directly on the GitHub repository.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do you rank or rate providers?</h3>
          <p>No. This directory contains structured factual information only. There are no ratings, scores, or freeform reviews. This is intentional — it prevents defamation and keeps the directory safe and trustworthy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can a provider request removal?</h3>
          <p>Yes. If a clinician or institution requests removal or correction, we handle it within 7 days. Contact us via GitHub Issues or email.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is this only for metros?</h3>
          <p>No. We welcome listings from any city in India. Teleconsult providers are especially valuable for people in smaller cities. Use the teleconsult filter to find them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How is data stored?</h3>
          <p>All data lives in a public <code>doctors.json</code> file in the GitHub repository. Every edit is tracked in git history. There is no database, no backend, and no API keys.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Why not just a Google Sheet?</h3>
          <p>A spreadsheet is tied to one person's Google account — if they leave, the data is stuck. A GitHub repo can be forked, transferred, and archived by anyone. Every edit has full version history, and every fork is a backup. Contributors don't edit raw data anyway — they use the submission form — so the "spreadsheets are familiar" argument doesn't apply here. GitHub gives us community ownership, resilience, and a clean way to power the frontend with a simple JSON file.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I use this data?</h3>
          <p>Yes. The data is released under the CC0 (public domain) license. You are free to use, share, and build upon it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section" style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>How to Contribute</h2>
      <div class="info-grid" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Submit a new listing</h3>
          <p>Use the <a href="/submit">submission form</a> to add a provider you know. Takes under 2 minutes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Report stale info</h3>
          <p>If a listing is outdated or incorrect, report it using the button on the listing page.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <h3>Help maintain</h3>
          <p>We welcome co-maintainers. Check the CONTRIBUTING.md on GitHub to get started.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="crisis-box">
        <h3>Crisis Resources</h3>
        <p><strong>iCall:</strong> 9152987821 (Mon-Sat, 8am-10pm)</p>
        <p><strong>Vandrevala Foundation:</strong> 1860-2662-345 (24/7)</p>
        <p style="margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.85rem;">If you or someone you know is in immediate danger, please call emergency services (112) or go to the nearest hospital.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-intro {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  }

  .faq-item h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .faq-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
</style>
